-hansi-theme-font:minor-latin;}\n</style>\n<![endif]--></p>\n<p>\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align: justify;">Because, even though there is a huge investment boom in tech and media in Russia and the C.I.S., it is still very much controlled by political and financial elites with embedded interests and, according to analysts, roughjy 90 percent of likely profitable ventures are 80 percent under-valued and lack the capital they need to succeed do primarily to lack of connections and mediators that help them make their companies appeal to Western investors.<span style="mso-spacerun:yes">&nbsp; </span>Likewise, wherease some years ago, it was primarily lack of rule of law that kept investors away from the market, today it has a lot more to do with lack of choice.<span style="mso-spacerun:yes">&nbsp; </span>Many investors want to be able to explore the markets thick and thin according to their specifically-designed citeria, as opposed to that developed by financial Western financial institutions that have become overly embedded in the local political and financial patronage networks, lack certain vision, and essentially allow only passive investment in what are essentially mutual funds.<span style="mso-spacerun:yes">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span>Investors want to invest in companies themselves, or with chosen like-minded partners, paired by Firebird, while they are at their lowest valuations.<span style="mso-spacerun:yes">&nbsp; </span>Many wish to explore confidentially, up until a certain point, which Firebird Speed allows.<span style="mso-spacerun:yes">&nbsp;&nbsp; </span>Finally, investors want to go face to face with the entrpreneirs and ask the questions that are significant to them.<span style="mso-spacerun:yes">&nbsp; </span>Firebird facilitates the face to face interaction from broad data bases and categories of vantures.<span style="mso-spacerun:yes">&nbsp; </span>Likewise, it assissts the Russian and C.I.S. companies packahe and present themselves in a manner that is comfortable to Western investors and, if required, monitor the entire investment process, working with lawyers to confirm the validity of all aspects of the company and paperwork involved and holding monies in FDIC-insured US-based escrow accounts until all equity has been handed over legally, as approved by the investor.<span style="mso-spacerun:yes">&nbsp; </span>Finally, Firebird still provides the opportunity for those investors who are more comfortable working from their armchairs and offices than bouncing about foreign lands while they are tugged at by groups with conflicting interests to calmly and, according to their own rules, control the speed and structure of the investment process without having to make tedious and oftentimes unfulfilling trips.<span style="mso-spacerun:yes">&nbsp; </span>Firebird provides an egalitariian meritocractic-based investment model of companies and investors of all shapes and sizes, allowing for politics, bureaucracy and other pressures to take a back seat to the main goal, which is to maximize the position of both the investor and entrepreneur via the investment and thus create a grass-roots investment climate based solely on worthwhile innovations and models and personalized finanicial evaluations.<span style="mso-spacerun:yes">&nbsp; </span>Add to this comfort of investment from home, saftey and security in financial transfers and documentation, assisstance in tranlsation and interpretation, targeted pairing of investors with interested companies and like-minded partners, and an emphasis on confidentiality.<span style="mso-spacerun:yes">&nbsp; </span>There are the advantages of Firebird Speed.</p>\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align: justify;">&nbsp;</p>\n</p>', 0, 1);
